"{\"uid\": \"ghanaiantimes.com.gh-gabby-thomas-claims-stunning-olympic-200m-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Gabby Thomas surged to victory of the women's 200m final on Tuesday night in Paris, winning wire-to-wire in 21.83 seconds.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999996578026, \"rank\": 3.420960078736384e-10, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 77, \"end\": 82, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999895275739555, \"rank\": 1.0472535664243223e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the process, she has claimed her Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 123, \"to\": 178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas led from the gun and finished with daylight between her and silver medalist, Julien Alfred, of Saint Lucia, who won 100m gold on Saturday.\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 179, \"end\": 185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999789338180347, \"rank\": 2.1066408723198076e-05, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am really in disbelief be\\u00adcause having an Olympic gold medal is something in my wild\\u00adest dreams,\\\" Thomas said.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 427, \"end\": 433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But at the same time I know how hard I have fought for it.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This has been six years in the making, head down, working hard.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas is joined on the medal podium by U.S. team\\u00admate, Brittany Brown, who earned bronze for her first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 565, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\", \"score\": 0.9999997142429446, \"rank\": 2.8573762634363924e-07, \"text\": \"Brittany Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown entered Paris with only one world medal (a silver from 2019 Worlds), and her 22.20-second dash around the purple Stade de France track has now added an Olym\\u00adpic bronze to her docket.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999895275739555, \"rank\": 1.0472535664243223e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_World_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999991885034, \"rank\": 8.1149659993808e-10, \"text\": \"2019 Worlds\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_World_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_World_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"or the race's emphatic victor, Thomas, this win comes after a string of falling short of gold in major title races.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the To\\u00adkyo Olympics, she took bronze.\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In her next big-ticket race, 2023 Worlds, it was a silver.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now in Paris, she's got her gold.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999895275739555, \"rank\": 1.0472535664243223e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the moment she landed in the City of Light, Thomas was the clear woman to beat.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The withdrawal of Jamaican rival, Shericka Jackson, only ballooned that target.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9992934734335175, \"rank\": 0.0007070188006318749, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympic title secures the 14th gold medal for the U.S. in the Olympic women's 200m, which breaks a 13-13 tie with Jamaica for the most in history (no Jamaican earned a 200m medal this year for the first time since 1976).\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999895275739555, \"rank\": 1.0472535664243223e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9993526670606168, \"rank\": 0.0006443532848244227, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9992934734335175, \"rank\": 0.0007070188006318749, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Thomas is the first Amer\\u00adican since Allyson Felix in 2012 to strike gold in the women's event.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 1562, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allyson Felix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old has endeared herself to the American public not just with her command of the track, but also with her extraordinary public health work.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999382244501018, \"rank\": 5.283476667273075e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She volunteers weekly at a Volunteer Healthcare Clinic (VHC) in Austin, Texas, which provides primary care to chil\\u00addren and adults without access to such care.\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1838, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9986254393657258, \"rank\": 0.0013764522525471833, \"text\": \"Austin, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\"}, {\"begin\": 1838, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9986254393657258, \"rank\": 0.0013764522525471833, \"text\": \"Austin, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a Harvard degree in neurobiology and global health, plus a master's in epidemiology from the University of Texas, Thomas is a safe bet to impact public health for decades after she stops running profession\\u00adally.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.9999936456099006, \"rank\": 3.137056066679585e-06, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas' subsequent dom\\u00adinance at Trials, where she posted a world-leading 21.78, sent her to Olympics No.\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2153, \"end\": 2159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, she has made good on the gold goal.\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas is a woman of many titles Harvard grad, healthcare worker, maybe even future doc\\u00adtor and now, she's earned the once-evasive designation of Olympic champion.-NBC\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2304, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9192101460902562, \"rank\": 0.08770134408959208, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.9999936456099006, \"rank\": 3.137056066679585e-06, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}]}]}"